            // Scholarships - Enhanced with detailed information
            'scholarship' => 'Scholarships are a great way to fund your study abroad journey! We offer various types including merit-based, need-based, country-specific, and specialized awards. Scholarships can cover tuition, living expenses, or both. What type of scholarship are you interested in? I can provide detailed information on eligibility, application processes, and tips to increase your chances.',
            'scholarships' => 'Our comprehensive scholarship database includes:\n\nâ€¢ Merit-based scholarships (for academic excellence)\nâ€¢ Need-based scholarships (for financial need)\nâ€¢ Full scholarships (100% coverage)\nâ€¢ Partial scholarships (25-75% coverage)\nâ€¢ Government scholarships (Chevening, DAAD, Erasmus+)\nâ€¢ University scholarships\nâ€¢ Sports scholarships\nâ€¢ Research scholarships\nâ€¢ Women and minority scholarships\nâ€¢ Study abroad specific scholarships\n\nMany cover 25-100% of tuition costs. Would you like details on eligibility criteria, application processes, or specific scholarship types?',
            'merit scholarship' => 'Merit scholarships reward academic excellence and achievements. \n\nEligibility:\nâ€¢ Minimum GPA: 3.0-4.0 (varies by program)\nâ€¢ Strong standardized test scores (SAT/ACT for undergrad, GRE/GMAT for grad)\nâ€¢ English proficiency (IELTS 6.5+ or TOEFL 80+)\nâ€¢ Leadership roles and extracurricular activities\n\nApplication Process:\n1. Submit academic transcripts\n2. Provide test scores\n3. Write personal statement\n4. Get letters of recommendation\n\nTips: Maintain high GPA, excel in tests, and demonstrate leadership. Many universities offer automatic merit scholarships upon admission.',
            'need based scholarship' => 'Need-based scholarships help students with financial difficulties.\n\nEligibility:\nâ€¢ Demonstrated financial need\nâ€¢ Family income below certain thresholds\nâ€¢ Academic merit (usually GPA 2.5+)\nâ€¢ Enrollment in degree program\n\nRequired Documents:\nâ€¢ Financial statements\nâ€¢ Tax returns\nâ€¢ Bank statements\nâ€¢ Essays explaining financial situation\n\nApplication Process:\n1. Complete FAFSA or equivalent form\n2. Submit financial documents\n3. Write need-based essay\n4. Provide income verification\n\nTips: Be honest about your situation and explain how the scholarship will help your education goals.',
