            'phd' => 'ğŸ”¬ PhD (Doctor of Philosophy)\n\nâ±ï¸ Duration:\nâ€¢ USA: 5-7 years\nâ€¢ UK: 3-4 years\nâ€¢ Europe: 3-5 years\nâ€¢ Canada/Australia: 4-6 years\n\nğŸ’° Funding:\nâ€¢ Most PhD programs FULLY FUNDED\nâ€¢ Stipend: $20,000-35,000/year\nâ€¢ Tuition waiver included\nâ€¢ Research grants available\nâ€¢ Teaching assistantships\n\nğŸ“š Popular Fields:\nâ€¢ STEM (Physics, Chemistry, Biology)\nâ€¢ Computer Science & AI\nâ€¢ Engineering (all streams)\nâ€¢ Social Sciences\nâ€¢ Humanities\nâ€¢ Business/Economics\n\nğŸ“‹ Requirements:\nâ€¢ Master\'s degree (preferred)\nâ€¢ Strong research background\nâ€¢ Publications (helpful)\nâ€¢ GRE (for some programs)\nâ€¢ Research proposal\nâ€¢ IELTS/TOEFL\nâ€¢ Strong recommendations from academics\nâ€¢ Faculty supervisor confirmed\n\nğŸ’¼ Career Paths:\nâ€¢ Academic positions (Professor)\nâ€¢ Research scientist (Industry)\nâ€¢ R&D leadership roles\nâ€¢ Policy advisor\nâ€¢ Average salary: $80,000-150,000\n\nğŸ“ Scholarships:\nâ€¢ Research assistantships (most common)\nâ€¢ Fellowships (NSF, NIH)\nâ€¢ Government scholarships\n\nğŸ”¬ Research Focus:\nâ€¢ Original contribution to field\nâ€¢ Publications required\nâ€¢ Dissertation defense\nâ€¢ Conference presentations\n\nInterested in specific research areas?',
            'courses' => 'ğŸ“š Course & Program Categories\n\nğŸ”µ STEM Fields:\nâ€¢ Computer Science & IT\nâ€¢ Engineering (20+ specializations)\nâ€¢ Mathematics & Statistics\nâ€¢ Physics & Astronomy\nâ€¢ Chemistry & Materials Science\nâ€¢ Biology & Life Sciences\nâ€¢ Environmental Science\n\nğŸŸ¢ Business & Economics:\nâ€¢ Business Administration\nâ€¢ Finance & Accounting\nâ€¢ Marketing & Sales\nâ€¢ Entrepreneurship\nâ€¢ International Business\nâ€¢ Economics\nâ€¢ Supply Chain Management\n\nğŸŸ¡ Arts & Humanities:\nâ€¢ Psychology\nâ€¢ English Literature\nâ€¢ History\nâ€¢ Philosophy\nâ€¢ Languages\nâ€¢ Communications\nâ€¢ Fine Arts\n\nğŸŸ  Health Sciences:\nâ€¢ Medicine (MD/MBBS)\nâ€¢ Nursing\nâ€¢ Public Health\nâ€¢ Pharmacy\nâ€¢ Dentistry\nâ€¢ Physical Therapy\n\nğŸ”´ Social Sciences:\nâ€¢ Sociology\nâ€¢ Political Science\nâ€¢ International Relations\nâ€¢ Anthropology\nâ€¢ Education\n\nğŸŸ£ Professional Programs:\nâ€¢ Law (JD/LLM)\nâ€¢ Architecture\nâ€¢ Design\nâ€¢ Hospitality\n\nWhat specific field interests you?',
            'programs' => 'ğŸ“ Available Program Levels\n\n1ï¸âƒ£ UNDERGRADUATE (Bachelor\'s):\nâ€¢ Duration: 3-4 years\nâ€¢ Entry: High school diploma\nâ€¢ Degrees: BA, BSc, BEng, BBA\n\n2ï¸âƒ£ GRADUATE (Master\'s):\nâ€¢ Duration: 1-2 years\nâ€¢ Entry: Bachelor\'s degree\nâ€¢ Degrees: MA, MSc, MEng, MBA\n\n3ï¸âƒ£ DOCTORAL (PhD):\nâ€¢ Duration: 3-7 years\nâ€¢ Entry: Master\'s degree\nâ€¢ Research-focused\n\n4ï¸âƒ£ PROFESSIONAL:\nâ€¢ MBA, Law (JD/LLM), Medicine (MD)\nâ€¢ Specialized training\nâ€¢ Industry certifications\n\n5ï¸âƒ£ DIPLOMA & CERTIFICATES:\nâ€¢ Duration: 6 months - 2 years\nâ€¢ Vocational & technical\nâ€¢ Career-focused\n\n6ï¸âƒ£ ONLINE & HYBRID:\nâ€¢ Flexible scheduling\nâ€¢ Global access\nâ€¢ Work while studying\n\nğŸ’¡ Program Selection Factors:\nâ€¢ Career goals\nâ€¢ Budget\nâ€¢ Duration\nâ€¢ Location\nâ€¢ Specialization\nâ€¢ Post-study work options\n\nWhich level interests you?',
            'stem' => 'ğŸ”¬ STEM Programs (Science, Technology, Engineering, Mathematics)\n\nğŸ’» Computer Science:\nâ€¢ AI & Machine Learning\nâ€¢ Cybersecurity\nâ€¢ Software Engineering\nâ€¢ Data Science\nâ€¢ Top Schools: MIT, Stanford, CMU, Toronto\nâ€¢ Average salary: $80,000-150,000\n\nâš™ï¸ Engineering:\nâ€¢ Mechanical, Electrical, Civil, Chemical\nâ€¢ Aerospace, Biomedical, Environmental\nâ€¢ Top Schools: MIT, Stanford, Berkeley, ETH Zurich\nâ€¢ Average salary: $70,000-120,000\n\nğŸ§® Mathematics & Statistics:\nâ€¢ Pure & Applied Mathematics\nâ€¢ Statistics & Data Analytics\nâ€¢ Actuarial Science\nâ€¢ Top Schools: Cambridge, MIT, Princeton\nâ€¢ Average salary: $70,000-110,000\n\nğŸ§ª Physical Sciences:\nâ€¢ Physics, Chemistry, Materials Science\nâ€¢ Research-intensive\nâ€¢ Top Schools: Cambridge, MIT, ETH Zurich\nâ€¢ Average salary: $60,000-100,000\n\nğŸ§¬ Life Sciences:\nâ€¢ Biology, Biotechnology, Biochemistry\nâ€¢ Genetics, Neuroscience\nâ€¢ Top Schools: Harvard, Stanford, Cambridge\nâ€¢ Average salary: $65,000-110,000\n\nğŸ’¡ Benefits:\nâ€¢ High demand globally\nâ€¢ OPT extension in USA (36 months)\nâ€¢ Strong job prospects\nâ€¢ Innovation opportunities\nâ€¢ Higher salaries\n\nğŸ“‹ Requirements:\nâ€¢ Strong math/science background\nâ€¢ Relevant undergraduate degree\nâ€¢ GRE (for graduate programs)\nâ€¢ Research experience (helpful)\n\nWhich STEM field interests you?',

            // Work Opportunities - Comprehensive Guide
            'work' => 'ğŸ’¼ Work Opportunities for International Students\n\nğŸ“š During Studies:\nâ€¢ USA: On-campus 20hrs/week, CPT for internships\nâ€¢ UK: 20hrs/week during term, full-time during breaks\nâ€¢ Canada: 20hrs/week during term, unlimited during breaks\nâ€¢ Australia: 48hrs/fortnight\nâ€¢ Germany: 120 full days or 240 half days/year\nâ€¢ Netherlands: 16hrs/week\n\nğŸ“ After Graduation:\nâ€¢ USA: OPT (12 months), STEM OPT (36 months total)\nâ€¢ UK: Graduate Route (2 years), 3 years for PhD\nâ€¢ Canada: PGWP (8 months-3 years based on program)\nâ€¢ Australia: 485 Visa (2-4 years based on degree)\nâ€¢ Germany: Job Seeker Visa (18 months)\nâ€¢ Netherlands: Orientation Year (1 year)\n\nğŸ’° Average Salaries:\nâ€¢ USA: $60,000-100,000\nâ€¢ UK: Â£25,000-45,000\nâ€¢ Canada: CAD $50,000-80,000\nâ€¢ Australia: AUD $60,000-85,000\nâ€¢ Germany: â‚¬45,000-70,000\nâ€¢ Netherlands: â‚¬28,000-50,000\n\nğŸ¢ Top Employers:\nâ€¢ Tech: Google, Microsoft, Amazon, Apple\nâ€¢ Finance: Goldman Sachs, JPMorgan, Citi\nâ€¢ Consulting: McKinsey, BCG, Bain\nâ€¢ Engineering: Boeing, Siemens, Tesla\n\nğŸ’¡ Tips for Job Search:\nâ€¢ Network early\nâ€¢ Attend career fairs\nâ€¢ Build relevant skills\nâ€¢ Get internships\nâ€¢ Use university career services\n\nWhich country interests you for work?',
            'job' => 'ğŸ’¼ Post-Study Work Visas - Complete Breakdown\n\nğŸ‡ºğŸ‡¸ USA - OPT (Optional Practical Training):\nâ€¢ Duration: 12 months (standard)\nâ€¢ STEM extension: Additional 24 months (36 total)\nâ€¢ Apply: 90 days before to 60 days after graduation\nâ€¢ Cost: $410 application fee\nâ€¢ Work: Full-time in field of study\nâ€¢ H1B transition possible\n\nğŸ‡¬ğŸ‡§ UK - Graduate Route:\nâ€¢ Duration: 2 years (Bachelor/Master), 3 years (PhD)\nâ€¢ No sponsorship needed\nâ€¢ Switch to Skilled Worker visa\nâ€¢ Work: Any field, any employer\nâ€¢ No minimum salary\n\nğŸ‡¨ğŸ‡¦ Canada - PGWP (Post-Graduation Work Permit):\nâ€¢ Duration: Matches program length (max 3 years)\nâ€¢ Programs 8-24 months: Same duration PGWP\nâ€¢ Programs 24+ months: 3-year PGWP\nâ€¢ PR pathway: Canadian Experience Class\nâ€¢ Spouse work permit available\n\nğŸ‡¦ğŸ‡º Australia - 485 Visa:\nâ€¢ Graduate Work: 18 months (Bachelor)\nâ€¢ Post-Study Work: 2 years (Master), 3 years (PhD)\nâ€¢ Regional: Additional 1-2 years\nâ€¢ PR pathways available\nâ€¢ Family can accompany\n\nğŸ‡©ğŸ‡ª Germany - Job Seeker Visa:\nâ€¢ Duration: 18 months to find job\nâ€¢ Convert to work permit after job offer\nâ€¢ EU Blue Card eligible (â‚¬56,800+ salary)\nâ€¢ PR after 33 months (21 with B1 German)\n\nğŸ‡³ğŸ‡± Netherlands - Orientation Year:\nâ€¢ Duration: 1 year\nâ€¢ No sponsorship needed initially\nâ€¢ Switch to Highly Skilled Migrant\nâ€¢ Salary requirement: â‚¬30,000+\n\nğŸ’¡ Maximizing Opportunities:\nâ€¢ Start networking early\nâ€¢ Gain relevant work experience\nâ€¢ Build professional profiles (LinkedIn)\nâ€¢ Attend industry events\nâ€¢ Consider multiple countries\n\nNeed help with job search strategies?',
            'opt' => 'ğŸ‡ºğŸ‡¸ OPT - Optional Practical Training (USA)\n\nğŸ“‹ Overview:\nâ€¢ Allows 12 months work in USA after graduation\nâ€¢ STEM majors: 24-month extension (36 total)\nâ€¢ Must be related to field of study\nâ€¢ Full-time or part-time allowed\n\nâ±ï¸ Timeline:\nâ€¢ Apply: 90 days before to 60 days after graduation\nâ€¢ Processing: 3-5 months\nâ€¢ Start work: After receiving EAD card\nâ€¢ Grace period: 60 days after OPT expires\n\nğŸ’° Costs:\nâ€¢ Application fee: $410\nâ€¢ STEM extension: $410 additional\nâ€¢ Premium processing: Not available\n\nğŸ”¬ STEM OPT Extension:\nâ€¢ 24 additional months (36 total)\nâ€¢ Employer must use E-Verify\nâ€¢ Formal training plan required\nâ€¢ Fields: Science, Technology, Engineering, Math\nâ€¢ Includes: CS, Engineering, Math, some Business programs\n\nğŸ“‹ Requirements:\nâ€¢ F-1 visa status\nâ€¢ Completed degree (Associate, Bachelor, Master, PhD)\nâ€¢ Work must be related to major\nâ€¢ Employer anywhere in USA\n\nğŸ’¼ After OPT:\nâ€¢ Apply for H-1B visa (lottery system)\nâ€¢ Consider other work visas\nâ€¢ Or return to home country\n\nâœ… Benefits:\nâ€¢ Gain US work experience\nâ€¢ Competitive salaries\nâ€¢ Path to H-1B and Green Card\nâ€¢ Build professional network\n\nNeed H-1B information?',
